# Comprehensive Research Paper Analysis

## 1. Confusion Matrix

```python
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Sample predictions and true labels
true_labels = [...]  # Replace with actual true labels
predictions = [...]  # Replace with actual predictions

cm = confusion_matrix(true_labels, predictions)
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt="d")
plt.title('Confusion Matrix')
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('True')
plt.show()
```

## 2. Cross Validation

```python
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score

model = ...  # Define your model here
scores = cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=5)
print('Cross Validation Scores:', scores)
print('Mean Score:', scores.mean())
```

## 3. Residual Plots

```python
import statsmodels.api as sm

# Fit the model
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Generate predictions
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

# Residuals
residuals = y_test - predictions
sm.qqplot(residuals, line='s')
plt.title('Residuals QQ Plot')
plt.show()
```

## 4. Model Comparison

```python
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error

models = [model1, model2, model3]  # List of models to compare
results = {}

for model in models:
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    preds = model.predict(X_test)
    mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, preds)
    results[model.__class__.__name__] = mse

print('Model Comparison:', results)
```

## 5. Error Distribution

```python
errors = y_test - predictions
plt.hist(errors, bins=30)
plt.title('Error Distribution')
plt.xlabel('Error')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.show()
```

## 6. SHAP Beeswarm

```python
import shap

explainer = shap.Explainer(model, X)
shap_values = explainer(X)
shap.plots.beeswarm(shap_values)
```

## 7. Learning Curve

```python
from sklearn.model_selection import learning_curve

train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(model, X, y, cv=5)

plt.plot(train_sizes, train_scores.mean(axis=1), label='Training score')
plt.plot(train_sizes, test_scores.mean(axis=1), label='Cross-validation score')
plt.title('Learning Curve')
plt.xlabel('Training Size')
plt.ylabel('Score')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
```